neighborhood_overview:
The north side is much cheaper than the city to buy groceries, and just about everything else! There are many shops and supermarkets and coffee shops that offer much better prices than in the city which I recommend using.

'Thrillist' have put Amsterdam North on number 3 in their list of the top 10 most 'hipster' neighborhoods on earth! It is surrounded by cool places to drink and party, and only a few minutes from the center.

Amsterdam Noord is currently being built into a 'Smart City' and so many new buildings and streets are being built within a sustainable concept, and interesting individual looking building are popping up all around the North area.

Here in the North side, it is possible to feel like a 'local', with local beers and organic food available in many local restaurants, bars and food/beer festivals.

There are also 2 coffee-shops within walking distance.

name: Cozy home & rooftop near center (6 adults& 2 kids)
description: Cozy apartment on the top floor of a typical late 1800s building in Amsterdam's lively neighborhood De Pijp, overlooking the beautiful Sarphatipark. Quiet, light, and very private for this area's standards because of its location, with a rooftop terrace. Beware of the STEEP stairs, though - my place is very comfy once inside, but you need to be rather fit and brave to haul your luggage upstairs. Also, note that Dutch houses were not built for hot weather and typically have no A/C.
neighborhood_overview: De Pijp is one of Amsterdam's hippest neighborhoods, with the highest density of stops, bars, and restaurants per square meter, plus the largest permanent street market right around the corner. You really don't have to leave the neighborhood; I seldom do. However, if you must visit Amsterdam's touristy highlights, they are all within reach. You can walk, bike or use public transport to any of them within 20 minutes.
host_about: Born and raised in Amsterdam, I set out to explore the world at a young age. Over the past four decades I have traveled to over thirty countries, and have lived in three of those. Currently, I am back at my habitat Amsterdam, where I am working as a self-employed co-creator (thecocreatorscom) and raising my three sons (13, 9, and 3 years old). Since 2021 I am also the co-ordinator of Wijkcentrum De Pijp, helping people improve our hood.

name: Big Warehouse apartment, Amsterdam
description:
I transformed a 250 m2 big industrial building into a creative playground for a group of friends. In Amsterdam North: the hip industrial area, where creativity is the new trend. You sleep in an old boatworkshop. It is designed to have fun.
There are 18 beds throughout the building.
neighborhood_overview:
The North of Amsterdam is a very trendy industrial area with a lot of artistic places to drink and dine in the neighbourhood. There is a good coffeshop at about 100 meters. A good Thai restaurant and Chinese takeaway around the corner.
Go to: De Ceuvel about 200 meters from the appartment. Go there for a nice breakfast or evening dinner and drinks in a super cool place.
Or go to de NDSM WHARF an old ship wharf with cafes/ restaurants like "Noorderlicht" or "Pllek": a restaurant built of old containers!
dont'forget to visit the centre of Amsterdam from time to time.

name: Beautiful renovated family house in Amsterdam East
neighborhood_overview:
Watergraafsmeer is a lovely residential area in Amsterdam Oost. It’s quiet, very green, and offers comfortable living in a safe and pleasant environment. When looking on a map of Watergraafsmeer, the wide and busy Middenweg cuts it in half.

To the east are the more popular 1930s developments with large and roomy apartments and family homes. You'll find some cosy bars, restaurants and small shops here which make this a great place to be. West of Middenweg is the spectacular Frankendael Park.

In between this mix are several village-like pockets with their own distinct feel. The most famous one is the architecturally important Betondorp, home of a young Johan Cruijff.

Along the charming Ringdijk canal one can still see traces of what the area was like before the 1930s building frenzy. The street that runs parallel to the canal is lined with elegant brick homes and trees and plants.

The zoo 'Artis', the National Maritime Museum, The Tropenmuseum

name: Gerenoveerd luxe 200m2 loft in het centrum!
neighborhood_overview:
The Singel was dug from the IJ to the Boerenwetering around 1428. Around 1450, the remaining part followed up to the Amstel. Until the city budget of about 1585, the Singel formed the western city border. From 1481, the ground floor was replaced by a stone wall. At that time, the Singel was also called Stedegracht. This Stedegracht now still consists of the current Singel, the Kloveniersburgwal and the Geldersekade.

In the 17th century, the Singel was called the Singel temporary King's cane as a tribute to King Henry IV of France; at the time a major ally of the Republic. The Koningsplein is still reminiscent of this.

The part of the Singel from the Round Lutheran Church to the Linese alley where the ships on London, the 'London skiers', had their mooring, were also called London Kaai and English Kaai. Between the Lijnbaanssteeg and the Torensluis, the Singel de Rouaansche Kaai was called the Singel de Rouaansche Kaai, because of the boat on the Canal.

In fact, I have been awarded the title of "Super Host" for 20 consecutive times, which is a testament to my commitment to providing a great experience for my guests.

Whether you're looking for a place to stay in Amsterdam or Bali, I have got you covered. I take pride in my listings and ensure that each one is well-maintained and well-equipped to meet all your needs. And, if you need any help or have any questions, I am always just a message away. So, don't hesitate to reach out to me if you need any assistance. I can't wait to welcome you to one of my amazing properties!

name: Spacious and luxurious apartment with sunny garden
description:
Spacious, luxurious (171sqm) and centrally located apartment at Amstel River. In “de Pijp”, Old South neighbourhood, close to the best bars, restaurants and Albert Cuyp market.

Our home, built in 1923, and has a monumental status. It was fully refurbished in 2020.

It's our family home, we only rent it out when we are on holiday ourselves. Please try to contact me directly. I'm the founder of touristdoc. I have a business profile on social media.

We prefer a couple or family with children
neighborhood_overview:
Located at Amstel River in the Old South (Pijp/Rivierenbuurt). Very close to all the best museums, restaurants and bars.

Very good connection with public transportation. Amstel train station is at walking distance.
host_about:
We are Peter and Marieke. we have been living in Amsterdam for more than ten years, before we gave up our lives there to live in New Zealand for a while. Since a couple of years we are back in Amsterdam, where we now live with our 2 daughters  (3 & 5 years old).

I (Peter) am working as a GP at my own practice in the city centre of Amsterdam and running my own company Touristdoc: (Website hidden by Airbnb)  Marieke works at a Family Fund that supports social enterprises & foundations within the sustainable food & energy transitions. 

PHILOSOPHY

A dutch saying: "Wie goed doet, goed ontmoet"

Translated: What goes around, comes around (but only in a positive way)

Interests

Peter: I love to do scuba diving and have a pint afterwards. If there's no diving spots around....just a pint. I'm attracted to most watersports actually. Sailing, surfing and swimming are fun too. Besides that I play field hockey and chess. I' ve been travelling to pretty much everywhere in the world and love to meet new cultures.

Marieke: also loves hobbies ;)

Music, Movies, and Books

I enjoy all kind of movies. Personal best would probably be Godfather 2.

I love electronic dance music like techno and deephouse and dance festivals, but anything with a beat or strong guitars will do.

I think I particularly enjoy world literature.

One Amazing Thing I’ve Done

Too much to mention: 
New York marathon. Diving trips all over the world. The culture shock in India.

Staying with Honduras' most popular pop artist.

Being invited to a family reunion with total strangers in Portugal.

We love travelling 

Countries We’ve Visited

Argentina, Australia, Austria, Belgium, Belize, Bonaire, Sint Eustatius and Saba, Brazil, Cabo Verde, Cambodia, China, Costa Rica, Cuba, Czech Republic, Denmark, Dominica, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, Egypt, England, Estonia, Fiji, France, Germany, Guadeloupe, Guatemala, Honduras, Hong Kong, Hungary, India, Indonesia, Ireland, Italy, Japan, Laos, Latvia, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg, Macedonia, Martinique, Mongolia, Morocco, Netherlands, Netherlands Antilles, New Zealand, Philippines, Portugal, Russia, San Marino, Scotland, South Africa, Spain, Thailand, Turkey, United Kingdom, United States, Viet Nam

Countries I’ve Lived In

Belgium, Netherlands, New Zealand

name: 380 sqm Villa in Amsterdam with 12 bedrooms!
description:
Welcome to our beautiful and spacious dual-home property, where you can enjoy the privacy of two separate homes connected by a common area. With a total of 12 bedrooms, our property is perfect for larger groups or families traveling together.

Each of our homes boasts six tastefully decorated bedrooms, complete with comfortable beds & high-quality linens Our homes are designed with cozy living areas, fully equipped kitchens, and dining areas perfect for hosting meals and gatherings.
host_about:
Hi, my name is Neal and I am the proud owner of Neal Estate. I have extensive experience traveling and working all over the world, with my base in Amsterdam. After hosting on Airbnb for over 10 years, I have honed my skills in making guests feel at home and providing top-notch service. In fact, I have been awarded the title of "Super Host" for 20 consecutive times, which is a testament to my commitment to providing a great experience for my guests.

Whether you're looking for a place to stay in Amsterdam or Bali, I have got you covered. I take pride in my listings and ensure that each one is well-maintained and well-equipped to meet all your needs. And, if you need any help or have any questions, I am always just a message away. So, don't hesitate to reach out to me if you need any assistance. I can't wait to welcome you to one of my amazing properties!

Our home is spread out over 4 floors and provides fantastic spacious accommodation for your visit to Amsterdam. There is plenty of space for you to spread out over the 3 double bedrooms 2 living areas and large open plan kitchen diner.

name: Stylish central apartment for family or 2 couples
description: The apartment, 3 floors, has all the comforts of a modern house. The light coming in is beautiful. Attention to detail and comfort, industrial/urban and situated in a quiet street in the green, cultural district called "The Plantage". It is a 5 to 10 minute walk to the very centre of Amsterdam, yet quiet and serene.
neighborhood_overview:
We love this area because you can walk out of the door and find within one minute: our favourite restaurant De Plantage, for breakfast and lunch Dignita Hoftuin and NewWerktheater (also for dinner on Thursday and Friday-evenings), the best ice creamshop, Coffee Company espresso cafe, the lovely Artis Zoo, the Hortus Botanicus, nice parks to have picknicks at the canal and the beautiful Portuguese Synagoge.

I am happy to share you with you all my personal recommendations to make your stay as enjoyable and authentic as possible.

De Plantagebuurt, at the east side of Amsterdam's city centre, is one of Amsterdam's greenest and prettiest areas, next to the Amstel River with its skinny bridge and the Hermitage Museum and also a 10 min. walk from the Waterloopplein, the Utrechtsestraat and the famous neighborhood the Pijp
with the University of Amsterdam opposite of the street (convenient for conference visits).
host_about: We are a family of four. Our daughter is from February 2015 and our son from July 2017. Julia (from 1978) is a teacher and Jelle  (from 1975) is an social entrepreneur in the restaurant and design business. We are fanatic cyclists in our spare time. We plan to take more time off from our busy lives to enjoy the time with each other and our children.

name: Artistic nest in De Pijp
description:
Our cozy and bright apartment is set in the local and vibrant area of De Pijp. The street is quiet and very well located:

- 1 min walking to the tram stop & bike rental shop.
- 1 min walking to the supermarket.
- 10 min biking to Museumplein and city center.

There is also a huge variety of nice restaurants, bars, and cafés within walking distance.

The tram line 4 goes through the city center all the way to the station.

name: Great family house (180m2) A'dam East with garden!
description:
This beautiful house is devided into three floors. Ground floor is the living room with kitchen and garden, 1st and 2nd floor is where the bedrooms and bathrooms are.
Enjoy this family house in the Watergraafsmeer, which is the centre of the upcoming Eastern part of Amsterdam. You will find lots of bars and restaurants in walking distance, or with the tram which starts around the corner.
neighborhood_overview:
The Watergraafsmeer is known for the spacious houses and relaxing atmosphere. Just a few minutes from the house there is the Frankendael park where you can relax and maybe have a great dinner in the famous restaurant De Kas. It is an old greenhouse, where they serve the best food ever.
Walk around and find more nice places in the neighborhood, or take the tram to go a bit further. Everything is closeby. Musea, the Zoo nice bars and restaurants, you name it. Also a small shopping area is only across the street.
host_about: We, Bart & Josepha are a couple who live in Amsterdam. We both work in Amsterdam and enjoy the city life very much! We have three beautiful children, Wolf, Maas and Teddy. Two years ago we bought this great house and renovated it completely. Since June last year we moved in and we are enjoying every bit of it. We are sure other people will enjoy it as much as we do.

name: 3-bedroom Family Apartment in trendy A'dam West!
description: Welcome in this comfortable large, quiet family apartment in a great (west) area of Amsterdam. There's a 120m2 private space with 3 bedrooms (1 for kids), a large bathroom and a large living room with a view on the canals where you can see the boats pass by. Restaurants, bars, Leidscheplein, De Hallen, Vondelpark and trams are all in walking distance. On request we have a parking spot available in the parking garage underneath the building. The apartment is 100% kids proof.
neighborhood_overview: You exit the apartment straight into the west side of Amsterdam. The Kinkerstraat, Jan Pieter Heijestraat and DeClerqstraat with all it's lively bars and restaurants are just around the corner.  'De Hallen' are about 5 minutes out and you can continue your stroll straight to Leidscheplein or Vondelpark. Right below the apartment is bar Kevin Bacon that offers great cocktails and nice Thai food. A couple of other places that are local and very nice: Buurman de With (pizza and beers), Benji's (Asian snacks) and Bar Spek (lunch and great coffee), but there are loads of other places as well. All local and not too 'touristy'.

name: Luxurious 112m2 ground floor appt
description: Chique and luxurious ground floor appartment with two bedrooms, huge living room gourmet kitchen, bathroom and small garden. Quiet location nearby the river 'Amstel', within walking distance from great city trips and bars/restaurants, close to public transportation. The perfect appartment for a couple with children! Our appartment provides sleeping space for five adults, or for instance three adults and two children, due to flexible sleeping options. We'd love to hear from you!
neighborhood_overview:
The impressive river 'de Amstel' is just at the end of the street. A gorgeous stroll alongside the river towards the trending and energetic area 'De Pijp' or the city centre shows you Amsterdam at her best!

Many restaurants and bars are within walking distance from the house. We will tell you which ones to visit to experience the real Dutch experience, and not the touristy one! :-) If you want to, we can help you with your reservations. Both higher end restaurants as informal places to eat are just around the corner.

A ten minute walk towards a big supermarket with anything you need: Albert Heijn.

The neighborhood is quiet. Sometimes on Friday and Saturday nights you will hear some noice of people walking towards the train station around 11pm/midnight. But it has never really bothered us.
host_about:
Hi fellow traveler! 

We are Bas and Mirte, around 35 yrs old and we live in Amsterdam with our two little kids ages 2 and 4.
Our motto for life is work hard, play hard: Mirte is a marketing manager in FMCG and Bas is owner of a paragliding school. Enough about work; we both love to travel, far away or closeby. Bas loves paragliding and visits the beach and dunes at least once a week to fly; even more he loves paragliding in the Alps, so if he's not enjoying Amsterdam; chances are you'll find him in Austria or Italy. I myself love cooking, running (great combination ;-)), shopping and reading. And I hate how boring my life looks compared to Bas' ;-). 
Oh and we do have other things in common, we both love watching movies and series! 

We bought our house in March '15. With an extensive renovation (in both time and euro's) we turned it into our perfect little Amsterdam-palace  and we treat it with care. We will take good care of your house, and expect you to do the same with ours.

name: Amsterdam city center & nature at your fingertips
description:
We love to welcome you to our warm, comfortable & spacious home in the safe and child friendly neighborhood Elzenhagen, an area located in the 7th most hip neighborhoods of the world, Amsterdam-North.

With the brand new subway near our house you're only 5 minutes away from Amsterdam Central Station. So you can enjoy the vibrant city of Amsterdam and the relaxing and peaceful atmosphere of our home and the Dutch countryside at the same time.
neighborhood_overview:
Our home in located the picturesque district 'Elzenhagen', with houses build in a very typical Dutch Zaanse style. It is perfectly located, with close by on the one hand central Amsterdam and on the other Waterland, the typical Dutch countryside. The charming villages and tranquil surroundings of neighbouring Waterland region make it a perfect destination for exploring by bike.

We will lay out two lists for you. One with our favorite places to visit in the center of lovely Amsterdam and one with our favorite spots in Amsterdam-North, the 7th most hip neighborhoods of the world, according to (URL HIDDEN)
"Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up!"
host_about:
Hi there!

We are a couple with a son, both working in the creative sector. While we love our life in Amsterdam, we've also fallen in love with the charm of southern Spain—the stunning nature, sunny weather, beautiful coastline & delicious food. ☀️

In 2022, we were thrilled to make a long-held dream come true by finding our perfect home near the coast in Estepona-Malaga.
We can’t wait to welcome you to our home, whether in Amsterdam or Estepona!

name: Spaceous apartment in Amsterdam-Noord
description:
Our apartment is particularly suited for families with 1 or 2 children.

Our large living room merges with the kitchen and is bathing in light, since our corner house has windows in virtually all directions. The second floor has 3 bedrooms (of which 2 children's bedrooms) and a bath room (with bath).

You'll be very close to the city centre : walk to the IJ-river and the ferry brings you to the heart of Amsterdam.

Enjoy Wifi, free car parking, and play the piano
neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam-North is especially fun, since it is THE upcoming area of the town. People of all sorts, finding their way, sharing their differences.
New, fresh, funny bars and restaurants are opening every day. Furthermore, it is among Amsterdam's 'greenest' areas, with parks and even a forest (hear 100's of birds singing).
With a 5 minutes walk, you'll find a lively atmosphere around the public swimming pool, the ice cream shop and the grass pitch.

name: Numa | XL 2-Bedroom Apartment w/ Sofabed
description: This comfortable apartment offers 81 sqm of space. Ideal for up to six people, its double bed (180x200), sofabed (160x200), two single beds (90x200), and modern bathroom with shower and bathtub make this stay a perfect way to experience Amsterdam. There’s also a kitchen and a dining table, so you’ll have everything you need for maximum comfort and minimal stress.
neighborhood_overview: Numa Amsterdam Docklands is nestled in the area of Amsterdam’s Eastern Docklands, which once played a crucial role in trade with the Dutch East Indies. Today, it’s home to chic, Scandinavian waterfront architecture. The area is rich in culture and dining options, boasting many of Amsterdam's most authentic restaurants and bars. Whether you’re a nature lover or an enthusiastic urban explorer, Docklands offers the best of both worlds. Just a short stroll away, you’ll find captivating, natural attractions–Flevopark, Artis Zoo, and the breathtaking Hortus Botanical Garden, one of Amsterdam’s greatest gems. Close to the botanical garden, you'll find the vibrant heart of Amsterdam at Rembrandtplein. Here, the selection of locally brewed beers is endless, and the lively energy of Amsterdammers immaculate.
host_about: In a world of stuffy, faceless hotels, we’re replacing the unnecessary hassle with simplicity and delight. Mixing technology and taste together in the world’s greatest neighbourhoods, we create stays that are unashamedly original authentic. With the comforts of home and the quality of a boutique hotel. Want to stay with us for longer? We’ve designed our properties with your joy in mind, whether you stay for a night, a week, or a season.

name: Generator - Private 6 bed Female Room
description: Experience privacy and comfort in our Female-Only Private 6-Bed Room at Generator Amsterdam. Designed exclusively for women, this room features 2 bunks (6 beds) and a private bathroom. Each bunk is equipped with a light, personal shelf, USB charging station, and under-bed lockers. A hair dryer is provided for your convenience. Pillow, duvet, and linen are supplied, with towels available at reception for a small fee.
neighborhood_overview: Generator Amsterdam is perfectly placed between Centrum and Oost boroughs, providing views of the Oosterpark’s scenic English garden right next door. From our budget hotel in Amsterdam it couldn’t be easier to get out and about; there’s ample public transport nearby to put you among the museums, music, nightlife and culture on offer in every corner.
host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

name: Generator - Superior Suite
description: Stay in our luxurious Superior Suite at Generator Amsterdam, featuring stunning treetop park views. This spacious suite includes a queen bed, 2 twin beds, and a sofa bed, accommodating your group in comfort. Enjoy the convenience of 2 private bathrooms, a living room with TV, and a kitchenette equipped with a mini fridge and dishwasher. Towels, toiletries, and a hair dryer are supplied. Plus, a charging station with USB port is provided for your devices.
neighborhood_overview: Generator Amsterdam is perfectly placed between Centrum and Oost boroughs, providing views of the Oosterpark’s scenic English garden right next door. From our budget hotel in Amsterdam it couldn’t be easier to get out and about; there’s ample public transport nearby to put you among the museums, music, nightlife and culture on offer in every corner.
host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

host_about:
We are a family of five:  us two, our 3 daughters plus two cats. Working both full time and pretty hard, so always very much looking foreword to holiday time, which isn't that easy to finance when traveling the regular way, staying in hotels etc. Our friends are so enthusiastic about AirBnB that we decided to join as well. When you think of it, it's crazy everybody's traveling leaving their own houses empty, renting cold and standard apartments en hotel rooms all around the world. So here we are!
We both work in the hospitality business ( Dorian is a chef and I'm hospitality manager at one of the greatest Concert halls in the world, the Concertgebouw). So what we like is obvious maybe: cooking and spending time with our friends and neighbors. But also in our little free time, reading, gardening ( me), running in the Vondelpark ( Dorian), watching series on Netflix ( only since a few months available here) and of course going on trips with our children. Preferably by train. Besides we don't own a car, it's just such a great way to travel.

name: Lovely light large houseboat for family/colleagues
description:
Wonderfully spacious colorful ark for a family or colleagues!
In the summer you can swim in front of the door or enjoy the sun on the terrace.
You can not only visit the city or events, but also stay at this special location.
You will quickly feel at home in our house on the water!
neighborhood_overview: We live 20 minutes from the center of Amsterdam in a special neighborhood: more than 100 houseboats are moored here!
host_about:
Hi, I’m Rosanne, living in a  ‘floating villa’ in Amsterdam and enjoying this every day.

I’m a mum of 4 (aged 18, 17, 12, 11) and teaching Dutch at secondary school/ high school is what I do for a living.

I love living on the water because of the feeling of freedom. Waking up, but not awake yet (…), I prefer sitting on my sup with my labradoodle Cooper and paddle relaxed across ‘De Nieuwe Meer’ to the ‘Amsterdamse Bos’, walking and playing there, take a swim and sup back to my house. 

When going on vacation, water is also almost always involved, from the beaches of  Dutch island ‘Texel’ to a stay at the harbour of Valencia. I also love citytripping, especially together with one of my girls.

NB: the watervilla is our house, we live here every day. Only when we go away for a vacation or short trip, it is available for AirBnb.

name: Unique house with garden in centre of Amsterdam
description:
Our three-floor house of 180 m2, built in 1860, is located in the heart of Amsterdam, in the green, cultural district called "The Plantage". Our street is widely believed to be the most beautiful street of Amsterdam. It is a 5 minute walk to the very centre of Amsterdam, yet quiet and serene.

Our house is a cosy, romantic, authentic and happy place. Quite unique!

The rule in Amsterdam is 4 guests max. Yet 2 adults with more than 2 kids won't be a problem. We have 6 places to sleep (3x2).
host_about:
We are a family from Amsterdam - Lodewijk (law professor) and Esther (practising lawyer) and four kids. We have been living in the centre for more than 25 years, we love the atmosphere of Amsterdam, take full advantage of what it has to offer culturally and also regularly go out into nature to go biking and cycling. 

We think it's a pitty our great house is just standing idly when we're not there, which is why we find airbnb such a great thing.

name: Nice family home in the trendy Noord district
description:
Charming family house with very green surroundings, located along a path without cars. A friendly, village-like neighbourhood in the trendy Noord district, praised by the New York Times as 'the ultimate place to be when you’re visiting Amsterdam'. With large, sunny garden. The front windows overlook the water, where ducks, herons and even kingfishers can be spotted.
Only 15 minutes away from the city centre. Use of our bicycles included (value +/- € 15,- per person, per day).
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighbourhood is in the historical quarter of Nieuwendam, in Amsterdam Noord. According to the New York Times, it is the place to be when you are visiting Amsterdam, with the renowned film museum and cinema Eye, trendy bars and restaurants (Ceuvel, FC Hyena, Skatecafé, Goudfazant, Noorderlicht, Café Modern, Pllek), festivals (food, music, theatre, etc.) and markets (vintage, Van der Pek market, IJ-hallen, Landmarkt etc.).
Our house is located in a very quiet spot just behind the dike with more beautiful old homes, at just a stone’s throw away from a lovely little harbour and Café Het Sluisje, with a cosy, sunny terrace by the water and local draft beers on tap. The lively city centre of Amsterdam, with the Rijksmuseum, Van Goghmuseum, The Nine Streets, restaurants, shops, theatres and the canals, is only 15 minutes away by public transport or car, or 20 minutes by bike and free ferry.
For your daily groceries, there is a large shopping centre (Buikslotermeerplein), which
host_about: The two of us are in our forties and we have two children, a 13-year-old girl and a 10-year-old boy. We love the city (theatre, museums, restaurants), but we also love nature (peace, green, water, preferably sea).

description:
The Koninginneweg, literally meaning the Queens Avenue, is one of Amsterdam’s most picturesque avenues. Situated in a massive two floor mansion with stately front entrance in elegant classic circa 1900 Amsterdam South apartment. This luxurious 145 m2 apartment offers an impressive garden, cosy Interior, massive lounge, ensuite terrace overlooking the impressive garde, art, in the high-end 'Sloan Square' district of Amsterdam at Vondelpark.

.
neighborhood_overview:
De buurt
The ‘Queens Avenue’ is located at the heart of old Amsterdam’s southern district. Located very near the distinctive Vondelpark, this area knows many fine restaurants, trendy bars and interesting shopping streets, such as the Cornelis Schuijtstraat.
The area also harbours many cultural highlights, including the Concertgebouw, Van Goghmuseum, Rijksmuseum and Stedelijk museum. Interesting nearby bars and restaurants (you may need to make reservations) are Mech, Bond, De Joffers, Pain Quotidien and Van Dam. The old south district is easy to reach by public transport and is regarded as one of the safest areas in Amsterdam

description:
Lovely, huge modern house with a garden in a charming neighborhood. Our house is especially suitable for couples, business people, and families, and it's wheelchair accessible (including an elevator). SPE
neighborhood_overview:
Do you want to enjoy the beautiful historical city center of Amsterdam, with its canals, pubs and museums, but also have a relaxing stay? IJburg is the place to be.

You can do your shopping at the nearby shopping centre, with two supermarkets, a bakery, butcher’s shop, fishmongers, pharmacy and local restaurants. We even have our own community store, selling products made by local artisans.

IJburg's location is not only practical, it is also beautiful as it is surrounded by water, natural parks and modern architecture. Also, it has a very nice city beach (Blijburg) with restaurants and pubs.

In the summer, you can have a swim in the lake or go to the harbor to rent a sailing boat, surf gear or a wakeboard. In the winter, if its cold enough, you can go ice skating on the canals of IJburg. Also, nature lovers can go for a run in one of the nice natural parks IJburg is surrounded with.

Kom langs en geniet van ons plekje ewaar we trots op zijn.
PS. het hele huis is drempellloos en rolstoeltoegankelijk.

name: Comfortabel schip Amsterdam
description:
Near the city center of Amsterdam, our comfortably authentic sailing ship is located. On the one hand you will see the bustling city and on the other hand you will see the rural area of Amsterdam Waterland, Durgerdam.
The ship is modern, contemporary and equipped with every comfort. The ship feels like a wonderfully spacious ship with a sustainable jacket. Thanks to the renovation that has been carried out in a sustainable way, you can enjoy all the comforts with peace of mind in summer and winter.
host_about:
In 2012 gooide ik het roer om. Na 15 jaar in loondienst en vijf jaar wonen en leven op het water.
Door mijn voorliefde voor alles rondom recreatie en watersport heb ik in dat jaar de stap genomen mijn droom werkelijkheid te laten worden en mijn eigen zeilcharterbedrijf Amsterdam-Sailing te starten.

Met mijn bedrijf wil ik mij richten op de kwaliteit van het leven, mensen een plezierige tijd en unieke ervaringen te laten beleven, vakmanschap en natuurlijk de zeilvaart.

Onze missie is om van ons schip een voorbeeld te maken in de zeilchartervaart op het gebied van duurzaamheid. Zo denken we bij de verbouwing van ons schip zoveel mogelijk in groene oplossingen, worden CO2-vriendelijke materialen gebruikt en nemen we energie- en waterbesparende maatregelingen.

name: Sleeping in a Church - Room for 5 at BUNK
description: After just minutes on the free ferry from Central Station, you’ll find Amsterdam’s true north. This up-and-coming neighbourhood is alive and kicking, bursting with cultural hotspots. At the centre of the neighbourhood’s social life there was always the Saint Rita church. Now that it is home to Bunk Amsterdam, this still holds true. Locals and travellers alike come to catch some rays on our terrace, sticking around for an affordable dinner and some free cultural nourishment.
neighborhood_overview: Just minutes by free ferry from Central Station lies Amsterdam North. This neighbourhood is alive and kicking, bursting with cultural hotspots. Authentic urban life lives on, too, still undiscovered by tourists.The Saint Rita church has always been a place where the North comes together. Now, it’s also where you’ll find BUNK Amsterdam. This monumental building is now home to 296 guests, 106 rooms, 50 private pods, eight communal dinner tables and one teddy bear. So come to the North Side, where we have cookies, and company. On top of that, you’ll be sleeping in a church, a unique experience in Amsterdam!
host_about:
BUNK bridges the gap between hotels and hostels by combining affordable luxury rooms and smartly designed private bunk beds.
We converted two monumental churches into meeting places for travellers, locals and artists alike. We host inclusive social events in our sustainable restaurant and other communal spaces.

We aim to redefine hospitality by creating a place for communal wonderment. Where those who wander will start to wonder, triggered by true art, honest food and sincere smiles. We make comfort and design available to everyone, without the need for deep pockets. name: Spacious family home (2 cats), centrally located
description: Feel welcome in our lovely family home in Amsterdam-Noord, 10 minutes from the city center (1 stop by metro), with great cafes, nice shops, trendy restaurants and a beautiful park around the corner.
neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam-Noord is the place where it is happening right now in Amsterdam. The newest and hippest restaurants are opening here, at the same time it is a relaxed place where a lot of families live and where you do not (yet) encounter crowds of tourists.

From our house you can walk to the Noorderpark metro stop in 5 minutes, where the metro will take you to the central station in 3 minutes and to all hotspots (Canal Belt, Anne Frank House, Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, etc) You can also walk to the ferry that will take you to CS over water in 3 minutes.

Our house is located in a very quiet street, but within walking distance are many cozy cafes with terraces, restaurants and fine shops. We've prepared a list of our favorite places for you. There is enough parking space in the street but is not free.

There is an (outdoor) swimming pool within walking distance, a beautiful park and for daily shopping there are enough supermarkets, bakeries, etc.

name: Generator - Superior Suite
description: Stay in our luxurious Superior Suite at Generator Amsterdam, featuring stunning treetop park views. This spacious suite includes a queen bed, 2 twin beds, and a sofa bed, accommodating your group in comfort. Enjoy the convenience of 2 private bathrooms, a living room with TV, and a kitchenette equipped with a mini fridge and dishwasher. Towels, toiletries, and a hair dryer are supplied. Plus, a charging station with USB port is provided for your devices.
neighborhood_overview: Generator Amsterdam is perfectly placed between Centrum and Oost boroughs, providing views of the Oosterpark’s scenic English garden right next door. From our budget hotel in Amsterdam it couldn’t be easier to get out and about; there’s ample public transport nearby to put you among the museums, music, nightlife and culture on offer in every corner.
host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

name: Comfortabel schip Amsterdam City
description: In the center of Amsterdam, our comfortably authentic sailing ship is located. The ship is modern, contemporary and equipped with every comfort. The ship feels like a wonderfully spacious ship with a sustainable jacket. Thanks to the renovation that has been carried out in a sustainable way, you can enjoy all the comforts with peace of mind in summer and winter.
host_about:
In 2012 gooide ik het roer om. Na 15 jaar in loondienst en vijf jaar wonen en leven op het water.
Door mijn voorliefde voor alles rondom recreatie en watersport heb ik in dat jaar de stap genomen mijn droom werkelijkheid te laten worden en mijn eigen zeilcharterbedrijf Amsterdam-Sailing te starten.

Met mijn bedrijf wil ik mij richten op de kwaliteit van het leven, mensen een plezierige tijd en unieke ervaringen te laten beleven, vakmanschap en natuurlijk de zeilvaart.

Onze missie is om van ons schip een voorbeeld te maken in de zeilchartervaart op het gebied van duurzaamheid. Zo denken we bij de verbouwing van ons schip zoveel mogelijk in groene oplossingen, worden CO2-vriendelijke materialen gebruikt en nemen we energie- en waterbesparende maatregelingen.

name: Beautiful, private home with porch and garden
description:
Our beautiful & private house is situated in a friendly urban area and has a nice rural feeling due to the iconic porch that wraps around our corner house. Surrounded by a beautiful garden and a basketball/soccer court and kids playground. Nature (Dutch windmills, forest, parks and lake) are right around the corner for stunning running or cycling tracks. You'll find yourself in the vibrant city-centre of Amsterdam in a 15 minute metro ride.
We only rent out to families, or adult groups <4.
neighborhood_overview:
Quiet area. It has a village vibe, but it's very close to the vibrant city centre and several beautiful nature destinations such as Abcoude (typical Dutch landscapes with windmills and farms), Diemerbos (forest), Gaasperplas (lake), Bijlmerweide (meadow). If you love sports you're definitely in the right spot.

At just a 5-10 minute bike- or busride you'll find the Bijlmer Arena area, with a big trainstation, game hall, imax cinema, concert halls, shops, restaurant and much more. There's a shopping centre at 5 mn bikeride called 'Amsterdamse Poort' where you'll find great food mostly from all African and Carribean culture, and nice (practical) shops.

name: 2 verdiepingen, 3 kamers in Amsterdam centrum
description:
In this centrally located accommodation, everything for your family is at your fingertips.

Wonderful location
neighborhood_overview:
Oud-West was a district of the municipality of Amsterdam in the Dutch province of North Holland from 1990 to 2010. As of 1 May 2010, it merged into the new West district.

The (former) district Oud-West is bordered by the Singelgracht (the border with Amsterdam-Centrum), the Vondelpark (the border with Amsterdam-Zuid), the Kostverlorenvaart (border with former district De Baarsjes) and the Hugo de Grootgracht (border with former district Westerpark).

The neighborhood that has grown from the nineteenth-century expansion districts along the Overtoom and Kinkerstraat.

Although there were (in 2007) 177 nationalities, Oud-West is not considered a "black" district. The political debate is limited to innocent topics such as whether trees should give way to create safe cycle paths, and the way in which the former Tollensstraat tramway depot had to be renovated.

In a broader sense, Oud-West also refers to all pre-war districts in West, including De Baa

name: Numa | Deluxe apartment in central Amsterdam
description: This spacious apartment with 2 bedrooms offers 90.6 sqm of space. Ideal for up to six people, its two double beds (180x200), sofabed (160x200), and two modern bathrooms with shower and bathtub make this stay a perfect way to experience Amsterdam. There’s also a kitchen and a dining table, so you’ll have everything you need for maximum comfort and minimal stress.
neighborhood_overview: YAYS Amsterdam North by Numa offers an authentic experience. The northern part of the city boasts captivating views over the Amsterdam waters. The neighbourhood is well-connected by public transportation, so you’re just a short ferry or metro ride away from Amsterdam Central Station. The area is home to attractive sights such as Nxt Museum, only a 9 min walk away from the apartments. EYE Filmmuseum and A’Dam Tower can be found near the closest ferry stop, both attracting tourists and locals alike. At NDSM Wharf, you'll find several hip cafés, art galleries and IJ-Hallen, the largest flea market in Europe, which is organized once a month. Despite its industrial history, the area has a warm and cosy charm, and became a highly sought-after neighbourhood to live in.
host_about: In a world of stuffy, faceless hotels, we’re replacing the unnecessary hassle with simplicity and delight. Mixing technology and taste together in the world’s greatest neighbourhoods, we create stays that are unashamedly original authentic. With the comforts of home and the quality of a boutique hotel. Want to stay with us for longer? We’ve designed our properties with your joy in mind, whether you stay for a night, a week, or a season.

host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located on the Keizersgracht canal, few meters from the bustling Utrechtsestraat with all its cafes, shops and restaurants.

Wake up in the morning and take in the views of the city, not before popping into a neighborhood bakery for breakfast croissants. In the evening, stroll along to one of the many nearby restaurants before enjoying a drink at a typical Amsterdam bruin café.

Walk just 100 meters, and you can find yourself on the Utrechtsestraat, renowned for its restaurants, cafes, designer boutiques, lovely bakeries and wine shops. The local feel of the Utrechtsestraat makes it an excellent option for tourists who want to become “Amsterdammers” (even if only for a couple of days). Plus, it’s a prime spot for hunting out the best and most original gifts to take back home.
For the partygoers, popular Rembrandt Square is only 300 meters away.
For exploring further afield, there is a tram stop just 50 meters away, with a direct line to bo
host_about:
Hey,

Welcome to Amsterdam, my idea of a user-friendly city!

Amsterdam is a lovely place to spend a few days in, particularly if you will be able to dive in to the local rhythm of life. 
Living in the 400 year old canal belt of Amsterdam allows one a fairytale like feeling, its a bubble of village life in a middle of a very modern and vibrant city. And this is the exact sensation we want our guest to experience.

After a decade of living in Aruba, Dutch Caribbean, we moved back to NL and were fortunate enough to "land" on the Amstel. 
You're very welcome to enjoy this beautiful part of Amsterdam from a fully private apartment. 

Cheers!

name: LOTUS, Classic Dutch Saling Barge
description:
Staying on our sailing ship is a truly unique experience, not only is it comfortable and one of the cheapest and nicest spots to stay with a larger group, it has everything you need while being away from home.
It's located in Amsterdams 'up & coming' NDSMdistrict, that's packed with old warehouses, graffiti arts and plenty of cultural cafes and restaurants, within walking distance.
The free ferry will get you from the ship to central station and thus downtown within 10 minutes.
neighborhood_overview:
The former NDSM Amsterdam ship wharf is a stunning hangout. Just 10 minutes by free ferry from Amsterdam Central Station.
A former shipyard located on the banks of the River IJ in Amsterdam Noord, the NDSM Wharf has blossomed into an enormous cultural hotspot in recent years with a vibrant artist community and an ever-expanding variety of bars and restaurants including a city beach with a stunning view on the Amsterdam skyline. With grounds exceeding the size of ten football pitches, the area hosts multi-disciplinary festivals, performances, exhibitions, dance parties and a wide range of other events in unique, post-industrial surroundings.
host_about:
I'm Olaf!
I'm the proud owner of two beautiful antique sailingvessels, which sail around Unesco's world heritage site: The Waddensea & it's islands, in summer.
In winter you are welcome to stay aboard of my ship the Lotus , while it’s moored in Amsterdam!

name: Numa | Comfy Duplex in Amsterdam East
description: This comfortable apartment offers 41 sqm of space. Ideal for up to six people, its two double beds (180x200 or 160x200), sofabed (160x200), living room, and modern bathroom with bathtub and shower make this stay a perfect way to experience Amsterdam. The apartment also offers a built-in kitchen and a dining table, so you’ll have everything you need for maximum comfort and minimal stress.
neighborhood_overview: YAYS Amsterdam East by Numa is situated in the Eastern Docklands area, a neighbourhood known for its rich maritime history and vibrant urban development. Within easy reach, discover attractions such as the Maritime Museum, NEMO Science Museum, and Wereldmuseum. For a dose of nature, take a relaxing stroll through Oosterpark, just 10 minutes away, and visit the nearby ARTIS Zoo and historic Hortus Botanicus, one of the world's oldest botanical gardens. In this neighborhood, you'll also find plenty of restaurants and cafés to choose from. Don't miss the opportunity to visit Brouwerij 't IJ, a renowned brewery, only a 5-minute walk away from your apartment. And with tram connections just around the corner, you can easily reach the city centre and Dam Square within a short 10-minute ride.
host_about: In a world of stuffy, faceless hotels, we’re replacing the unnecessary hassle with simplicity and delight. neighborhood_overview: YAYS Amsterdam Salt House Canal by Numa is located on one of the many artificial islands the city of Amsterdam was built on. This western area known for its salt warehouses in the 18th century, is a favourite among locals, especially local artists. Just a few minutes’ walk away, you’ll find Haarlemmerstraat and Jordaan District–both famous for housing unique galleries, vintage shops, lively cafés, quirky museums, and authentic local businesses. Every Saturday, you can enjoy a flea and farmers’ market in Noordermarkt . They’re always bustling with people, searching through collections of antiques, books, vintage fashion, as well as organic products such as cheese, honey, and much more. For a good laugh, you can’t miss the opportunity to visit Boom Chicago. Here, the exhilarating performances, quick wit and sharp writing guarantee a night full of joyful tears. Experience the most authentic sides of Amsterdam while staying at YAYS Amsterdam Salt House Canal by Numa!

neighborhood_overview: Generator Amsterdam is perfectly placed between Centrum and Oost boroughs, providing views of the Oosterpark’s scenic English garden right next door. host_about: Generator Amsterdam is located in the up-and-coming eastern side of the city, overlooking Oosterpark. This former zoological university building can accommodate 564 guests in 168 twin and quadruple rooms, with en-suite bathrooms and incredible views of the surrounding area. There is also one luxury apartment for six people, with views of the park and a self-catered kitchen. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. We’ve turned the former lecture hall into an impressive chill-out lounge and bar, while the old library is now a relaxation and private events room. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

name: House Boat in Amsterdam outside city centre
description:
Our modern two story house boat is located in a residential area with a large garden and big terrace whilst only 20-25 minutes bike ride from the Vondelpark and 30 minutes by boat to the famous canals.

The house boat is fully kids safe and suitable for families. Swimming in the water, or bycicling to the recreational area Oeverlanden and Lake the Nieuwe Meer for more swimming. The Northsea Beach is 30 mins by car.

No groups and we prefer families
neighborhood_overview:
The house boat is located in a quit area on the Ringvaart van de Haarlemmermeer on the outskirts of Amsterdam. If you want the bustling city life this isn't the place to be. It is approximately 20-25 minutes by bike from the Vondelpark and public transportation is available into the centre of town.

The Ringvaartdijk is a dead end street with only local car traffic. There are a lot of pedestrians/runners and byciclists using it as it connects and is close recreational areas (Oeverlanden, Nieuwe Meer). The Amsterdamse bos is only a ferry ride away and great to take kids on a bicycle tour.

Going into the city is convenient by bike and the bike lanes are fully separated from the car lanes all the way into the city centre which makes it more safe.
host_about: Na een wereldreis zijn wij (Bas 47, Winni 45, Pleun 6 en de konijnen) begonnen met het bouwen van onze boot (of eigenlijk woonark). We wonen er nu inmiddels al weer 2 jaar en thuiskomen voelt alsof we op vakantie gaan. Gisteravond na het werk zijn we weer in de Ringvaart gesprongen. Vanavond bootje varen en weer zwemmen.

name: Family home in North-Amsterdam!
description: A beautiful family house located in the fantastic neighborhood of Amsterdam-Noord. The perfect base for exploring Amsterdam. The house is situated in a quiet and peaceful neighborhood, with trendy restaurants, museums, a park and shops close by. The house features three spacious and bright bedrooms, as well as a backyard where you can enjoy breakfast in the sun. We have decorated the house with a lot of love and care, and we hope our visitors will treat it with the same level of respect.
neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Noord is the northern district of Amsterdam, situated on the opposite bank of the IJ River from the city center. It is an up-and-coming neighborhood that has undergone significant redevelopment in recent years, transforming from an industrial area to a creative and cultural hub. The district is known for its trendy cafes, hip restaurants, and art galleries, as well as its diverse cultural offerings.

Some of the notable attractions in Amsterdam Noord include the EYE Filmmuseum, a modernist building dedicated to the art of film; the NDSM Wharf, a former shipyard turned creative hotspot featuring street art and a flea market; and the A'DAM Lookout, an observation deck offering panoramic views of the city. There are also several parks in the area, such as the Noorderpark and the Vliegenbos, which provide ample opportunities for outdoor recreation.

One of the unique characteristics of Amsterdam Noord is its accessibility. The district is connected to the city

neighborhood_overview:
The Riekerpolder is a polder in the municipality of Amsterdam, district of Nieuw-West (before 1921 municipality of Sloten), north of the Nieuwe Meer.

The Riekerpolder is a continuation of the Rietwijkerpolder and the Bovenwegse Sloterpolder (or Sloterbuitenpolder) and was created in 1636 when the area between the Sloterweg and the Nieuwe Meer was diked and drained with a polder mill, the Riekermolen. The polder is part of a peat meadow area that was part of the Hollands-Utrecht peat area.

The pastureland thus created remained intact for centuries. During the reclamation of the Haarlemmermeer (1849-1852), a part of the polder in the southwest was excavated for the Ringvaart of the Haarlemmermeerpolder, between where Badhoevedorp and the hamlet of Nieuwe Meer are now located.

The Sieger Park has been located along the Sloterweg since the 1930s. There are also allotments ('Ons Buiten'), which have been established here since 1927, and there is the Sportpar

neighborhood_overview:
The Watergraafsmeer is a polder in the Netherlands. It was reclaimed in 1629. In the 17th and 18th centuries, there were many buitenplaatsen in the Watergraafsmeer, though nowadays only one, Frankendael, remains.

Since 1921, the Watergraafsmeer is part of the city of Amsterdam and its rural character has all but disappeared. It is located in the borough of Amsterdam-Oost. The most important streets in the Watergraafsmeer are the Middenweg and the Kruislaan.

neighborhood_overview:
We are on the site of an awesome urban farming project, you'll find fields with crops, pigs, chickens, a restaurant, a veggie take-away, kids daycare, natural play ground, woodworking, natural playground, a beekeeper, a wine yard and a brewery. And plenty of space to play.

The hustling and bustling NDSM wharf with is only 15 minutes away by bike, from here the ferry to Central Station departs. Fifteen minutes biking in the other direction you can find nature area 'het Twiske' where you can swim, bike and hike. Only 10 minutes by foot you can discover the hidden nature area of 'Noorder IJplas'. The Zaanse Schans, IJselmeer, beach and 'bollenstreek' are easy to reach.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam (Pontsteiger) - From the northern Pontsteiger, you are in the city in no time. The nearby Westerpark blends green spaces, a lively creative and nightlife scene, and iconic architecture. Along with its regular exhibitions, markets and festivals, the converted Westergasfabriek gasworks contains indie shops, eclectic eateries, an art-house cinema, a brewery and a dance club. Nearby, the Museum Het Schip is the focus of a residential area of red-brick Amsterdam School buildings.
host_about: I live in Amsterdam, either on our family owned sailing ship Chateauroux or on my private sailing ship. In the summers I'm often out sailing on the Dutch waters (or beyond!). I also own a coworking space and coffee bar called BounceSpace in the city centre of Amsterdam. You're welcome to come by there for coffee or for a work spot. I"ll be happy to tell you more about living on a ship in Amsterdam and of course where to go during your stay :)

description: Have fun with the family at this modern gem. Located in the Rivierenbuurt is a newly renovated first floor corner apartment boasting tons of light. neighborhood_overview:
Located in the family-oriented Rivierenbuurt, the peaceful neighborhood has a picturesque main square with bakeries, cafes, restaurants, grocery stores and shops. Our delicious go-to's are Grammes (croissants), Scandinavian Embassy / Brandmeester (coffee), and Patisserie Tout (desserts). Parks, playgrounds and an indoor pool are within a short walking distance.

The Pijp is within a 15 minute (1km) walk, boasting the largest open-air market (Albert Cuyp) and tons of lively bars, restaurants and shops.

The RAI conference center is a 10 minute walk and the nearest train station / metro. For those with a vehicle, there is also a large parking lot there for long-term parking.

Public transport is easily accessible with bus and two tram lines leaving right outside the door/1 block away.

Schiphol airport is a 12 minute drive or 30 minutes by tram/train.

Street parking is paid parking (except Sundays) and fairly easy to find on our street.

Welcome! Comfortable freestanding home, spacious retreat 15 minute bike ride from Central Station. The house is a former industrial space, 280m2.
Private garden and parking. 4 bedrooms. 2 bathrooms. Oasis in Amsterdam city.
Big garden, BBQ. Perfect for families who like the city but also appreciate some quietness! Free use of our bikes. Free towels, linen.
neighborhood_overview: Our neighbourhood is in the sunny side of the river IJ that crosses Amsterdam. Amsterdam's north side is undergoing a rapid transformation of gentrification where industry, varying from wharves to small scale car shops, is making place for houses. Our specific neighborhood has been residential since the early 20th century. Although in our street there are three older farms, one going back as far as the 17th century. It has a very cosy and private feeling, with many gardens, an old dyke, a canal and it still has a certain rural atmosphere. But as said before; Central Sation is 15 minutes by bike, from there on you easily walk or bike almost anywhere in Amsterdam since it is a very compact city. You can obviously also connect to almost all trains, trams, busses and metro.

name: AMAZING PRIVATE LUXURY BOAT ACCOMMODATION!
description:
"Sailing barge Egberdina" is over a century old. During her long life she has explored the Dutch waters carrying cargo and goods from one place to the next.

Nowadays she has been refitted to accommodate groups of passengers. With a luxury design that is reminiscent of the early 1900's, she provides a place to stay, unwind and relax.

The atmosphere makes you wonder about the adventures of earlier days, the life people must have lived and all the unknown shores this ship must have visited..
neighborhood_overview:
The Eastern islands of IJburg are a wonderful place in Amsterdam. They are located to the east of Amsterdam and provide excellent accessibility of the historic city center as well as the beaches out to the east.

The tram that takes you to Amsterdam central station in 17 minutes stops at a distance of about 4 mins walk.

The beach club of Blijburg is located at a 15 minute walk and the beaches of the IJ-lake or the Amsterdam lakeside are right around the corner at a distance of 5 mins walking.

There is a lovely boulevard with great restaurants and bars located right in front of the boat as well as several companies that rent out gear for watersports.

Ijburg is a lively community that provides it all, water, beaches, sports and activities as well as a direct connection to the historic city center of Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview:
The Riekerpolder is a polder in the municipality of Amsterdam, district of Nieuw-West (before 1921 municipality of Sloten), north of the Nieuwe Meer.

The Riekerpolder is a continuation of the Rietwijkerpolder and the Bovenwegse Sloterpolder (or Sloterbuitenpolder) and was created in 1636 when the area between the Sloterweg and the Nieuwe Meer was diked and drained with a polder mill, the Riekermolen. The polder is part of a peat meadow area that was part of the Hollands-Utrecht peat area.

The pastureland thus created remained intact for centuries. During the reclamation of the Haarlemmermeer (1849-1852), a part of the polder in the southwest was excavated for the Ringvaart of the Haarlemmermeerpolder, between where Badhoevedorp and the hamlet of Nieuwe Meer are now located.

neighborhood_overview:
The family town house is located right in the middle of q safe, friendly, and upmarket area of the city; Amsterdam Old South/Museum Quarters. The best -and quickest- way to get around town is by bike. However, all major points of interest are within walking distance and easily accessible by local transportation:
- Van Gogh- and Rijksmuseum: 10-minute walk / 5 minutes by bike
- The Vondelpark: 3-minutes walk / 2 minutes by bike
- Albert Cuyp market: 15-minutes walk / 10 minutes by bike
- Upcoming and hip neighborhood De Pijp, with its many concept stores, bars, restaurants, and terraces is only 15-minutes walk / 10 minutes by bike
- Canals in the city centre: 15-minutes walk or tram / 5-minutes by bike
- Convention Centre RAI: 20-minutes walk / 10 minutes by bike
- Tram-stop (line 2 to city centre) is a 1-minute walk
- Bus-top (line 397) direct to/from Schiphol Airport is a 5-minutes walk.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in Oud-Zuid which is one of the boroughs of Amsterdam. The Museum Quarter (Museumplein) with the Stedelijk Museum, Van Gogh Museum, and the Rijksmuseum, belongs to Oud-Zuid.

Oud-Zuid is home to Amsterdam's most luxury shopping street -- the PC Hooftstraat -- which features high-end clothing (Chanel, Gucci, Hermés, Louis Vuitton), jewelry (Chopard, Cartier) and specialty (Mont Blanc, Henckels) stores, as well as several boutiques selling more luxury labels.
The Van Baerlestraat features chic names like Pauw and Vanilia. Beethovenstraat, along the eastern border of this neighborhood, boasts a row of women's, men's and children's chic shops. Don't miss Cornelis Schuytstraat and its trendy boutiques and home stores for a special Dutch outfit or gift.

Hi, my name is Neal and I am the proud owner of Neal Estate. I have extensive experience traveling and working all over the world, with my base in Amsterdam. After hosting on Airbnb for over 10 years, I have honed my skills in making guests feel at home and providing top-notch service. In fact, I have been awarded the title of "Super Host" for 20 consecutive times, which is a testament to my commitment to providing a great experience for my guests.

Whether you're looking for a place to stay in Amsterdam or Bali, I have got you covered. neighborhood_overview:
The Riekerpolder is a polder in the municipality of Amsterdam, district of Nieuw-West (before 1921 municipality of Sloten), north of the Nieuwe Meer.

The Riekerpolder is a continuation of the Rietwijkerpolder and the Bovenwegse Sloterpolder (or Sloterbuitenpolder) and was created in 1636 when the area between the Sloterweg and the Nieuwe Meer was diked and drained with a polder mill, the Riekermolen. The polder is part of a peat meadow area that was part of the Hollands-Utrecht peat area.

The pastureland thus created remained intact for centuries. During the reclamation of the Haarlemmermeer (1849-1852), a part of the polder in the southwest was excavated for the Ringvaart of the Haarlemmermeerpolder, between where Badhoevedorp and the hamlet of Nieuwe Meer are now located.

The Sieger Park has been located along the Sloterweg since the 1930s. There are also allotments ('Ons Buiten'), which have been established here since 1927, and there is the Sportpar

name: Off the beaten track: quircky place in green area
description:
Enjoy a very special green setting on the edges of Amsterdam. A sustainable place to stay, to play and to relax. Not too far from the city, yet tranquille and lots off space.

If you come for a drugs vacation, please find another place to stay. This place is not suited for that, we don't allow the use of marihuana at our premesis.

Please read our COVID-19 measures in the description beneath.
neighborhood_overview:
We are on the site of an awesome urban farming project, you'll find fields with crops, pigs, chickens, a restaurant, a veggie take-away, kids daycare, natural play ground, woodworking, natural playground, a beekeeper, a wine yard and a brewery. And plenty of space to play.

The hustling and bustling NDSM wharf with is only 15 minutes away by bike, from here the ferry to Central Station departs. Ten minutes biking to the other side you can find nature area 'het Twiske' where you can swim, bike and hike. Only 10 minutes by foot you can discover the hidden nature area of 'Noorder IJplas'. The Zaanse Schans, IJselmeer, beach and 'bollenstreek' are easy to reach.

name: Amsterdam Farm Lodge: spacious and parentfriendly
description:
Experience this 'off the beaten track' accommodation just on the outskirts of Amsterdam. 'Amsterdam Farm Lodge' is a haven for those seeking a sustainable stay, offering a basic but comfortable and spacious accommodation. Nestled within the innovative urban farming project, 'NoordOogst', the lodge offers an escape from the city's hustle and bustle without straying too far away from its joys.
Please note that we're not located directly in the city center so check our location before booking.
neighborhood_overview:
We are on the site of an awesome urban farming project, you'll find fields with crops, pigs, chickens, a restaurant, a veggie take-away, kids daycare, woodworking,, a beekeeper, a wine yard and a brewery. And plenty of space to play.

The hustling and bustling NDSM wharf with is only 15 minutes away by bike, from here the ferry to Central Station departs. Fifteen minutes biking to the other direction you can find nature area 'het Twiske' where you can swim, bike and hike. Only 10 minutes by foot you can discover the hidden nature area of 'Noorder IJplas'. The Zaanse Schans, IJselmeer, beach and 'bollenstreek' are easy to reach.

neighborhood_overview:
The Riekerpolder is a polder in the municipality of Amsterdam, district of Nieuw-West (before 1921 municipality of Sloten), north of the Nieuwe Meer.

The Riekerpolder is a continuation of the Rietwijkerpolder and the Bovenwegse Sloterpolder (or Sloterbuitenpolder) and was created in 1636 when the area between the Sloterweg and the Nieuwe Meer was diked and drained with a polder mill, the Riekermolen. The polder is part of a peat meadow area that was part of the Hollands-Utrecht peat area.

The pastureland thus created remained intact for centuries. During the reclamation of the Haarlemmermeer (1849-1852), a part of the polder in the southwest was excavated for the Ringvaart of the Haarlemmermeerpolder, between where Badhoevedorp and the hamlet of Nieuwe Meer are now located.

The Sieger Park has been located along the Sloterweg since the 1930s. There are also allotments ('Ons Buiten'), which have been established here since 1927, and there is the Sportpar

name: Cosy & Comfortable sailing boat for your own!
description:
Welcome to this sailing ship from 1897 in Amsterdam, and now functioning as a group-accommodation at a spot where it's hip!
In the summer months, the boat sails on the Wadden Sea as a charter. With a cosy interior and pleasant atmosphere you feel at home right away. The NDSM area is a new hotspot of Amsterdam, in a view minutes you walk to the free ferry's which will take you to the centre of Amsterdam! Hope to see you aboard!
neighborhood_overview:
The Boreas is located on a private jetty on the authentic old shipyard the NDSM-wharf in Amsterdam North. You are only 9 minutes away from central Amsterdam by ferry.

The NDSM area emerged the last five years as one of the hippest and most creative neighborhoods in Amsterdam. In the summertime there are festivals organised every weekend, and in the winter there are all creative and cultural events in the huge warehouses.
The location is awesome - you can take the ferry for free wich leads you directly into the centre. Still there are very cool bars and restaurants right next to the boat. Two minuter wal from the boat you will find Cafe Noorderlicht, an organic restaurant that already had sustainability and bio-products before it became a trend. In the evening they often have bands. Slightly further you will find Plek, a restaurant built from shipping containers, with great food and good music.
At the departure site of the ferries there is fine bakery Brood.
host_about:
Hello I'm Grietje!

Together with my husband Henk we have this beautiful ship. It's an old ship from 1897. In the old days this boat had cargo on board and sailed across the sea from Holland to Denmark and Sweden.

Nowadays we are sailing in the Summer with groups of people on board who have a sailing holiday and in the winter we are moored in the beautiful city of Amsterdam. We stay here on one spot. I like to have people on board who enjoy being together.

 I am a woman of the sea and everything that has to do with water has an enormous attraction on me! I love life and take care of myself by eating healthy food, walking in nature with our dog and practice yoga, and sail in the summer of course!

Carpe Diem!

So when you want a nice and special place in the World city of Amsterdam, come on board and feel at home on our ship! We are pleased to welcome you!

Your hostess Grietje

neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in the south part of Amsterdam. In this fascinating neighborhood, history fuses with contemporary culture. A large proportion of Amsterdam’s cultural attractions are clustered in the south, as well as some of the best shops and foodie hotspots. A day in Amsterdam Zuid can be spent admiring artworks from the Dutch Golden Age, singing along with the world’s biggest pop stars and sampling the latest food trends.

Oud Zuid is home to the world-renowned Rijksmuseum, the Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum and Moco Museum in the aptly named Museumplein: a grassy public square bustling with visitors taking photographs. Adjacent to the museums is the Royal Concertgebouw, a prestigious classical music venue that also invites the public to attend free lunchtime concerts every Wednesday. It has flexible and spacious social areas, filled with creative design touches like glass-fronted elevators, a light and airy café and an outdoor terrace. The basement and café are now dining destinations and the original boiler room has become a secret late night bar.

neighborhood_overview:
Within walking distance is a large supermarket (1 min) and a bathing jetty (1min). It is a child-friendly neighborhood with many playgrounds in each courtyard. Cafes and restaurants can be found at the NDSM hotspot (15 min walk).

This area is called the Bongerd (orchard of apple trees) and is part of the bigger area ‘Tuindorp-Oostzaan’ (garden village). Bongerd means orchard, so all our streetnames are names of different sorts of apples, like our street ‘Kaneelappelstraat’ (apple cinnamon street).This neighbourhood has been built in the last 7 years.

We live very close to the NDSM-wharf, which is in the Top-10 of the hippest area's in Europe. This used to be a harbour. You can still see an old crane at the end of the street, which had been used for building 80% of the houses that are in this area as of the 1950s. Our neighbourhood is trying to preserve & restore the old crane. You can find really good restaurants in the most spectacular places. You can have a par
host_about:
Hello there!

My husband - Frans - and I have been living in Amsterdam for over 10 years. For us it's the most wonderful city to live in!

I'm Belgian and Frans is a Dutchman. Together we've done quite some traveling. We met in Mallorca, lived together in Ghent, Belgium for 3 years, lived in Istanbul, Turkey for 1/2 year, extensively travelled through Italy & Spain and in 2013 we came back from a 1 year trip around South-America. Though having seen all these beautiful places, Amsterdam has stolen our hearts and we can't imagine living anywhere else but here. Cycling through the city, across the bridges and next to the canals always puts a very large smile on our faces! 

We invite you to come and explore all the magic this city has to offer!

Elien & Frans

host_about:
Hello,
We love AIrbnb. It is a great concept. We are proud te be a member of this community and love to explore the world at other Airbnb nice places. We introduce ourselves.
We arrived in Amsterdam in 1992 ( Michiel) and 1994 (Marlous) for doing our study and since then we didn’t leave this amazing city (except all the travels and work experiences abroad) so we discovered the city at early age ( with experiencing all the good and bad things), started our career over here and now we have our family life in this lovely neighborhood which feels like a modern upgraded ghetto in the middle of the energetic city of Amsterdam.

We enjoy our family life with the kids who goes to school and has there friends nearby and playgrounds are all over around (our garden, “Vondelpark”, “Museumplein”) and within a second we leave the house for a movie (at Cinecenter Cinema near "Leidseplein" is our favorite) or a theatre (Stadsschouwburg at "Leidseplein" which also has lots of International Plays) or having drinks with friends in one of the bars or restaurant nearby (the “Pijp” or the Jordaan”). All within a short distance or a 10 or 20 minute walk. 

We love to work hard as an Photographer and an Advocate and doing sports like racecycling, jogging, yoga and we all play tennis. We do love art and painting. We loved to travel around the world and now with our kids we downsized the distance to overcome and explore Europe with his nice countries like Italia (our favorite till so far is the lovely place Lucca) and Austria (for skieing and staying in a nice family village like Zell am See), Turkey (with the charming surfing hotspot of Alacati) and our favorite cities like Paris ( we love to eat a croissant with our kids in Parque Luxembourg) and Tarifa (for hanging around in this kite-surfing place paradise). We also enjoy simply going to the nearby beaches of Bloemendaal (Beachclub Republiek), Zandvoort ( Family Beach Vooges) or Noordwijk (Beachclub Zuiderbad) and we love to overstay a weekend in our familyhouse in Zeeland. We enjoying life with our friends and being with our lovely kids.

We are also interested in Houseswap with another family for a nice place which is child friendly, has 5 beds available, situated nearby sea and beach or nice cities in Europa, a lovely apartment in New York or anything special and authentique. Don't hesistate to contact us!

host_about:
We are a family with 3 children and we welcome you to one of our family houses in the Netherlands or France. 

Our family is keen on comfort and relaxation and we love many possibilities of a big city like Amsterdam nearby. We truly love the dynamics and history of Amsterdam. We have a comfortable and spacious house, equipped with all conveniences, centrally located in the Netherlands and the city center close by. A great house to plan your trips in the Netherlands and also an unique place to start exploring Amsterdam.

During the holiday season we are true nature lovers, that is why we have completely rebuilt an original farmhouse, located in the beautiful and peaceful surroundings of the famous Cantal, part of the Auvergne France. 

The Auvergne region, also known as the lungs of France, is a varied region in terms of landscape. No monotony here: volcanoes, forests, plains, mountains and valleys, often with rugged untouched nature. We love cycling, hiking, tennis and good regional products! 

We wish you a warm welcome in one of our family houses!

name: Volledig duurzaam authentiek schip Amsterdam
description: On the enchanting island of NDSM lies Bracksand, a more than 120-year-old two-masted sailing clipper. Despite his age, Brackand is modern, contemporary and fully equipped. Bracksand feels like a wonderfully spacious large ship with a durable jacket. Thanks to the renovation that has been carried out in a sustainable way, you can turn on the underfloor heating with peace of mind and enjoy the fresh ventilation that blows through the cabins.
neighborhood_overview:
"All you need is already there." And that doesn't apply to all of us. You don't have to go far to see beauty! Because even if the ship stays in its beautiful place, there is so much to do. Once you step off the ship, you'll fall into the heart of the iconic and centrally located NDSM grounds. It's awkward, crowded, and cinematic. Bracksand is located on the "Green Cape", a part of the NDSM where you can record the rawness and history of the harbor area with all your senses. In the 1950s, NDSM was one of the world's largest and forefront recruiters! And this history can still be seen everywhere.

The four immense docks on the island can accommodate countless studios and nesting towns. For example, NDSM is a place for many artists, summer events and cozy festivals. Continuous companies such as MTV, Greenpeace are also located on this pure piece of Amsterdam. The Veronica boat is also there this summer, with open-air movie nights.
