host_about:
In 2012 gooide ik het roer om. Na 15 jaar in loondienst en vijf jaar wonen en leven op het water.
Door mijn voorliefde voor alles rondom recreatie en watersport heb ik in dat jaar de stap genomen mijn droom werkelijkheid te laten worden en mijn eigen zeilcharterbedrijf Amsterdam-Sailing te starten.

Met mijn bedrijf wil ik mij richten op de kwaliteit van het leven, mensen een plezierige tijd en unieke ervaringen te laten beleven, vakmanschap en natuurlijk de zeilvaart.

Onze missie is om van ons schip een voorbeeld te maken in de zeilchartervaart op het gebied van duurzaamheid. Zo denken we bij de verbouwing van ons schip zoveel mogelijk in groene oplossingen, worden CO2-vriendelijke materialen gebruikt en nemen we energie- en waterbesparende maatregelingen.

name: Glamping lodge Amsterdam city 2
description: Camping among the trees in the middle of the city with the comforts of home. The camping feeling but not the hassle. Sleeping under canvas in a real bed and waking up to the singing of birds and the croaking of frogs. Making a cup of coffee in the kitchenette and enjoying it in the sun on the veranda in front of the tent. By bus or bicycle, you can be in the centre of Amsterdam within 25 minutes. Bikes can be rented at reception and the bus stop is an 8-minute walk away.
neighborhood_overview: What makes it so nice to spend the night at our campsite? Well, that's different for everyone. Some like all the greenery on and around the campsite, others love the fact that you can get to the centre of Amsterdam so quickly. Some can't get enough of the woodpecker sounds or the hooting of an owl, while others can't wait to discover the catering establishments around us. Basically, we are lucky enough to be located in the Tuinen van West, one of Amsterdam's last undiscovered gems, from where you can reach the city centre in no time. Get on the bus or bike and before you know it, you're strolling along our centuries-old canals. Tired from an exciting day in the city in the evening? Then plop down next to the campfire and doze off with the croaking of frogs in the background.
host_about: Ik ben Arnoud Lips. Keuzes maken is altijd lastig voor me geweest. Daarom ben ik ooit Economie gaan studeren omdat je daarmee nog alle kanten op kon. Daarna ben ik in de journalistiek beland, heb ik een eigen sportmarketing bureau gehad en twee keer een eigen Horeca gelegenheid. Toen liep ik tegen deze camping aan en dat is voor mij echt een schot in de roos. Dit is het helemaal en hier wil ik oud worden. Het liefst met al mijn gasten..;-)

name: Relaxing Well located Apt - Amsterdam
description: Welcome to my lovely apartment. This beautiful, light and comfortable space is conveniently located in Amsterdam city. A  perfect place for couples or people on business trips. Literally across the street from RAI convention center and financial WTC, it is also surrounded by plenty of great  restaurants, cozy brunch cafes, and the best ice cream shop of Amsterdam. Next door you can find the green and relaxing Beatrix Park.  Just rent a bike next door and enjoy the full Amsterdam experience.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in the picturesque Rivierenbuurt neighbourhood of Amsterdam. The neighbourhood is situated in Amsterdam-Zuid, bordered by the river Amstel to the east, the Boerenwetering canal in the west, the Amstelkanaal in the north and the A10 motorway in the south.

The neighbourhood features many fine examples of Amsterdam School-architecture. The Dutch word Rivierenbuurt translates as 'Rivers Neighbourhood', which refers to the fact that most streets in the area are named after rivers in the Netherlands.

The apartment is literally across the street from the RAI convention center, very close to the train station and the metro 52, which takes you to the busiest centre of Amsterdam, literally in 7 minutes.
The apartment is also situated across the street from the finest restaurants and bars (best fish restaurant in town!).
host_about:

love traveling, living in different places and experiencing new cultures... that’s why Amsterdam is the city to be in.
As hobbies, apart from traveling I love diving, cooking (with nice music on), reading  books, do some (amateur) oil painting or just  going for long walks and picnics in Beatrix park (just next to my house) ...
Also like decoration and making my house  nice and cozy.
With friends we often indulge in a grilled meat or fish meal in restaurants nearby accompanied by a cold bottle of white wine. 
For travel or for work, come and try the true Amsterdam life,  I have a bunch of good tips for you :) Have fun!

Frankendael, now turned over in a great restaurant (do eat lunch on their wonderfull terrace in summer) on the Middenweg, is the one example that has survived. There's a wonderfull garden and town park adjacent.
You don't even have to go to the citycenter to spend a wonderfull time in Amsterdam: the Watergraafsmeer (and the other eastern parts of Amsterdam) is a very popular neighbourhood, full of hipster cafés and trendy restaurants, a list of which we will provide. You can look for great architecture at the nearby Indische buurt, and the Eastern Islands. There are great parks to relax and sport close by: the kid friendly Frankendael, the Flevopark (great for running) and Oosterpark.

neighborhood_overview:
The Riekerpolder is a polder in the municipality of Amsterdam, district of Nieuw-West (before 1921 municipality of Sloten), north of the Nieuwe Meer.

The Riekerpolder is a continuation of the Rietwijkerpolder and the Bovenwegse Sloterpolder (or Sloterbuitenpolder) and was created in 1636 when the area between the Sloterweg and the Nieuwe Meer was diked and drained with a polder mill, the Riekermolen. The polder is part of a peat meadow area that was part of the Hollands-Utrecht peat area.

The pastureland thus created remained intact for centuries. During the reclamation of the Haarlemmermeer (1849-1852), a part of the polder in the southwest was excavated for the Ringvaart of the Haarlemmermeerpolder, between where Badhoevedorp and the hamlet of Nieuwe Meer are now located.

The Sieger Park has been located along the Sloterweg since the 1930s. There are also allotments ('Ons Buiten'), which have been established here since 1927, and there is the Sportpar

neighborhood_overview:
We have lived in several beautiful places in Amsterdam, but this is our favorite, ideal location. That's because of the lovely spacious, bright and cozy house, where everyone feels right at home and welcome. Second, its central location is perfect. It has the statity of the chic Oud-Zuid and the liveliness of Oud-West.
The neighborhood has everything you want in Amsterdam. The streets surrounding the Vondelpark are beautiful with many trees and stately houses. You will walk right into the Vondelpark for a nice walk and a nice cup of coffee or lunch on a beautiful terrace. All the major museums (Van Gogh, Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk Museum) and the famous Concert Hall are within a 10-minute walk, as are the upscale P.C. Hooftstraat where all the big brands sit.
If you walk a little further, you are already in the popular De Pijp district, full of restaurants and cafes.
If you walk the other way, you'll be in Oud-West, one of the nicest and liveliest neighborhoods in Amsterdam.

name: Glamping lodge Amsterdam City 3
description: Camping among the trees in the middle of the city with the comforts of home. The camping feeling but not the sores. Sleeping under the tent canvas in a real bed and waking up to the singing of birds and the chatter of frogs. Put a cup of coffee in the kitchen and drink it in the sun on the porch in front of the tent. Both by bus and bicycle, you can be in the heart of Amsterdam city center within 25 minutes. Bicycles are available for rent at the reception and the bus stop is an 8-minute walk.
neighborhood_overview: What makes it so nice to stay at our campsite? Well, that's different for everyone. One loves all the greenery and around the campsite, the other loves that you are so quickly in the center of Amsterdam. One does not get enough of the knocking of a woodpecker or shouting an owl and the other can't wait to discover the restaurants around us. It actually boils down to the fact that we are lucky to be in the Gardens of West, one of the last undiscovered gems of Amsterdam, from where you are also very quickly in the center. You get on the bus or by bike and before you know it you can walk past our centuries-old canals. In the evening tired of an exciting day in the city.? Then plop next to the campfire and go to sleep with the chatter of frogs on the background.
host_about: Ik ben Arnoud Lips. Keuzes maken is altijd lastig voor me geweest. Daarom ben ik ooit Economie gaan studeren omdat je daarmee nog alle kanten op kon. name: Glamping lodge Amsterdam city 1
description: Camping among the trees in the middle of the city with the comforts of home. The camping feeling but not the sores. Sleeping under the tent canvas in a real bed and waking up to the singing of birds and the chatter of frogs. Put a cup of coffee in the kitchen and drink it in the sun on the porch in front of the tent. Both by bus and bicycle, you can be in the heart of Amsterdam city center within 25 minutes. Bicycles are available for rent at the reception and the bus stop is an 8-minute walk.
neighborhood_overview: What makes it so nice to stay at our campsite? Well, that's different for everyone. One loves all the greenery and around the campsite, the other loves that you are so quickly in the center of Amsterdam. One does not get enough of the knocking of a woodpecker or shouting an owl and the other can't wait to discover the restaurants around us. It actually boils down to the fact that we are lucky to be in the Gardens of West, one of the last undiscovered gems of Amsterdam, from where you are also very quickly in the center. You get on the bus or by bike and before you know it you can walk past our centuries-old canals. In the evening tired of an exciting day in the city.? Then plop next to the campfire and go to sleep with the chatter of frogs on the background.

name: Numa | Family Maisonette in central Amsterdam
description: This comfortable maisonette offers 85.3 sqm of space. Ideal for up to six people, its double bed (160x200), sofabed (160x200), two single beds (80x200), and modern bathroom with shower make this stay a perfect way to experience Amsterdam. There’s also a kitchen and a dining table, so you’ll have everything you need for maximum comfort and minimal stress.
neighborhood_overview: YAYS Amsterdam Salt House Canal by Numa is located on one of the many artificial islands the city of Amsterdam was built on. This western area known for its salt warehouses in the 18th century, is a favourite among locals, especially local artists. Just a few minutes’ walk away, you’ll find Haarlemmerstraat and Jordaan District–both famous for housing unique galleries, vintage shops, lively cafés, quirky museums, and authentic local businesses. Every Saturday, you can enjoy a flea and farmers’ market in Noordermarkt . They’re always bustling with people, searching through collections of antiques, books, vintage fashion, as well as organic products such as cheese, honey, and much more. For a good laugh, you can’t miss the opportunity to visit Boom Chicago. Here, the exhilarating performances, quick wit and sharp writing guarantee a night full of joyful tears. Experience the most authentic sides of Amsterdam while staying at YAYS Amsterdam Salt House Canal by Numa!

name: Industrial Warehouse apartment, Amsterdam
description:
In an industrial building I created a spacious apartment in its former industrial style. It's like you are staying in a workshop. Oil-drum kitchen, rusty chandelier, old wooden bar, beds made of scaffolding wood, chains and paint cans everywhere.
You will also find an (amateur-) pool table, double showers for romantic showers together and a terrace with BBQ in front of the building. There also is a free private parking space. And last but not least you will have your own roof terrace!!
neighborhood_overview:
We are located in an ndustrial area. Very practical when you want to hang out and have fun in your own private warehouse. It is located on just 7 minutes cycling to Central Station. Or you can take the free ferry or bus 34 . It is just 2 stops to the Central Station.
Shopping center Mosplein is 200 meters from the apartment , there you,ll find 2 big supermarkets.
A coffeeshop is only 100 meters away ( to buy all sorts off smokeries)
And a Chinese take away is next door.
The Ceuvel across the street and canal. For diner and lunch. It has a good bar as well. Great atmosphere.
Also the NDSM , is 500 meters to the left. To the end of the Papaverweg. A Big creative industrial terrain with good bars and restaurants like Noorderlicht or PLLEK with good food in a creative restaurant . You have never seen a restaurant like this. Pllek is made out of containers and Noorderlicht is a restaurant made of..... ehhh sand bags and flexible see through plastic.... a play gro

neighborhood_overview:
This beautiful apartment can be found in the south of the city to the immediate west of the beautiful Amstelpark. The park is the perfect place to enjoy a picnic and grab some quiet time with a good book under any of the thousands of tall trees. The park also incorporates a restaurant, a playground, some galleries, and a mini golf course known locally as ‘midget golf’. Make your way through the park to discover a beautiful authentic windmill alongside the stunning River Amstel. Why not hire bicycles and cycle across the park emerging alongside the river? You can follow it south to the pretty town of Ouder Amstel. On your way there you will pass through open countryside, experience beautiful wildlife and breathe lots of fresh air. Enjoy a beer and an ice cream and cycle back into along the opposite side of the river. It makes an excellent afternoon excursion for all the family.

host_about:
Hi I'm Nancy. Together with my husband Arthur we are Airbnb hosts. 
Arthur will welcome our guests and can tell you much about the neighborhood. Why are we host? Because we really like to meet new people. But also it's nice to show our beautiful city.
 
We have two daughters. One of 16 years and the other is 11 years. We have a dog Rakker, where we enjoy hiking.

neighborhood_overview:
Combine the magic of Amsterdam with the serenity of this tranquil location, renowned for its avantgarde architecture!
IJburg is one of the safest, most stress-free spots in Amsterdam, 12 minutes by tram from the center, the tram going often. The house is on one of the loveliest streets of IJburg, with practically no traffic at all; all you hear at night are the ducks in the canal down below. neighborhood_overview: YAYS Amsterdam Prince Island by Numa is situated on one of Amsterdam’s Western Isles. It’s a historic neighbourhood, renowned for its canals and small drawbridges. Apart from its history, the neighbourhood takes pride in its large number of popular artist studios and exclusive homes. At Haarlemmerstraat, only a 4 min walk away from the property, you’ll find a variety of local restaurants and a great selection of boutiques. Famous attractions such as the Anne Frank House and Amsterdam Tulip Museum are just a few minutes’ walk down the canals. On your way to the attractions, you can explore the Joordan area, which offers eye-catching views and appealing amenities.

name: Ruime gezinswoning met tuin
description:
Wonderful spacious and cozy family home in an ideal location. Quiet and "hidden" among the greenery, but close to the hustle and bustle of the city. neighborhood_overview:
Centrally located in a quiet, child-friendly residential area, at the edge of the Amsterdamse Bos, close to the Rai, the Zuidas and Amsterdam Zuid.

Within walking distance is a cozy little square with shops, restaurants and a supermarket.
There are excellent and fast public transport connections to downtown Amsterdam. The cozy city center of Amstelveen is also located in the nearby area. Tram stops within walking distance. Highway easily accessible.

Our house is hidden between the countryside, with the nature reserve Het Groene Lint right behind us. There is no traffic at the front door. The garden is located to the south and is very sunny and green. Lots of privacy! Between the apple and pear trees, you can go barbecuing. The garden offers a variety of lounge facilities and a tropical cabin where you can chill out.

We live in our house. If you like "sleek", this might not be the best choice. Those who love coziness will not be disappointed.

name: Unique spacious (private) boat in Amsterdam.
description:
"Sailing barge Titaan” is a relatively new ship in the Dutch fleet. She is build in 2001 and has been used mostly for romantic sailing trips and weddings.

Nowadays she has been refitted to accommodate groups of passengers (up to 12 people). The traditional white sailing barge in combination with a more modern and luxury interior gives the whole ship an interesting twist and a perfect place to unwind and relax.
neighborhood_overview:
The ship is moored in the marina of IJburg. Characteristic of IJburg is that it's located on an archipelago of artificial islands in the IJmeer. As a result, the ship is right next to (or should we say in) the IJmeer, and makes you simply a few minutes away from beautiful nature reserves. The swamp forest 'Diemer Vijfhoek' is a well-known one, where the alternation of wetlands, open water and reed lands make it a true bird paradise. You can walk here from the boat in 20 minutes.

Fort Island Pampus is a stone's throw from the venue. The ferry service to Pampus departed just around the corner.

Craving an adventure a bit more far away? Polder IJdoorn and Vuurtoreneiland are located slightly to the north of the location and can be reached via Zeeburg. Here you can walk beautifully and enjoy the unique flora & fauna.

Still looking for the crowds? Amsterdam is less than 20 minutes away.

neighborhood_overview:
Spiegelkwartier

The Spiegelkwartier is the Art and Antiques district in Amsterdam.
Here you’ll find more than 70 antiques dealers and art galleries, together offering a resplendent array of fine historical objects, classic and contemporary art, and exotic folk art.
You will find also restaurants, casual eateries and cosy cafés on almost every corner.
The Spiegelkwartier is located between the Herengracht and the Rijksmuseum.


Museum Quarter

The Amsterdam Museum Quarter is home to the three most important museums in the Netherlands: the Rijksmuseum, the Stedelijk Museum and the Van Gogh Museum.
It also houses the majestic Concertgebouw and some superb cafés and restaurants.
With its large grassy open area, the Museumplein offers plenty of room to have a picnic or just relax. The Museum Quarter even has its own indoor swimming pool.
And a visit isn’t complete without posing with, or on, the giant Iamsterdam sign.
